HEADWORD: Incontrovertible
<hw>In*con`tro*ver"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
controvertible; too clear or certain to admit of dispute;
indisputable.</def> <au>Sir T. Browne.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>In*con`tro*ver"ti*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*con`tro*ver"ti*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

